<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1897-04-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1897-04-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="250" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d250">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Sherman</persName> to Sir
                                    <persName type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1897-04-16"><hi rend="italic">April 16,
                                1897</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 643.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have pleasure in confirming and
                            repeating the oral assurance heretofore given you, that the Government
                            of the United States will welcome the visit of Professor Thompson to the
                            Pribilof <pb facs="0303" n="269" xml:id="pg_269"/> Islands, and that
                            orders will at once be issued to the authorities on the islands to
                            extend to him the same facilities granted him during his visit last
                            year.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Sherman.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>